One important thing: once those YAML files exist, the generator will use them instead of the built-in fallback. So all six files need to be present and valid.

For Phase 4B, expected result is:

Developer Workstation Installs
Security Baseline Installs
Security + LUKS Installs
Embedded / Edge Hardware Installs
Minimal Installs
Small Disk Installs
Utilities / Rescue
Drop to iPXE shell

And only Minimal Installs should generate real boot targets. The other profiles should still be safe “not implemented” placeholders.

So: Dockerfile path looks good, folder/file names look good, but fill the YAML files before building.